EmailTemplate.name: 2015 Ag Outreach
EmailTemplate.subject: Dimagi Biz Dev Meeting - Ag Solutions for Development
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Hi there,
Sorry to email you out of the blue, but I’m writing to see if you’d like to meet on March 26 or 27th to discuss the use of mobile technology for agriculture.
I’m the Partnerships and Development Manager (DC-based) for Dimagi, a social enterprise that deploys open-source cloud-based software for extension workers, primarily in low- and middle- income countries. We have about 200 active projects, and partner with organizations such as Save the Children, World Vision, CARE, etc.
While we’ve focused primarily on health, over the last two years we have been growing our projects in agriculture. As you can see from the attached write-up, we have dozens of active agriculture projects in 11 countries.
Our Chief Strategy Officer and lead on Ag will be visiting DC from our headquarters in Boston on May 26 and 27. We’ll be giving a brownbag at the USDA on the morning of the 26th. Please let me know if you might be interested in us visiting while down there or setting up a call sometime to discuss how we might collaborate.
Best, Steve
